"703","<PAGE>"
"704","                              AMENDED AND RESTATED"
"705","                                     BY-LAWS"
"706","                                       OF"
"707","                   THE TRUSTS IDENTIFIED ON APPENDIX A HERETO"
"708","                                    ARTICLE I"
"709","                                   DEFINITIONS"
"710","        The   terms   Commission,  Declaration,  Distributor,  Interested
Person,  Investment  Adviser,   Majority   Shareholder  Vote,  1940  Act,"
"711","Shareholder,  Shares,  Transfer  Agent,  Trust,   Trust  Property  and"
"712","Trustees have the respective meanings given them in the Amended  and  Restated"
"713","Declaration  of  Trust of the Trusts identified on Appendix A hereto. References"
"714","to a Trust mean  each  Trust severally and not jointly. These By-Laws shall be"
"715","subject to the Declaration for all purposes."
"716","                                   ARTICLE II"
"717","                                     OFFICES"
"718","        SECTION  1.  PRINCIPAL  OFFICE.  Until  changed  by  the  Trustees,  the"
"719","principal office of the  Trust  in The Commonwealth of Massachusetts shall be in"
"720","the City of Boston, County of Suffolk."
"721","      SECTION 2. OTHER OFFICES. The  Trust may have offices in such other places"
"722","without as well as within The Commonwealth  of Massachusetts as the Trustees may"
"723","from time to time determine."
"724","                                   ARTICLE III"
"725","                                  SHAREHOLDERS"
"726","        SECTION 1. MEETINGS. Meetings of the  Shareholders  may be called at any"
"727","time by a majority of the Trustees. Meetings of the Shareholders for the purpose"
"728","of considering the removal of a person serving as Trustee shall be called by the"
"729","Trustees  if they are requested in writing to do so by Shareholders  holding  in"
"730","the aggregate  Shares representing not less than ten percent (10%) of the voting"
"731","power of the outstanding  Shares  of  the  Trust  having voting rights. Any such"
"732","meeting  shall be held within or without The Commonwealth  of  Massachusetts  on"
"733","such day and at such time as the Trustees shall designate."
"734","        SECTION  2.  NOTICE OF MEETINGS. Notice of all meetings of Shareholders,"
"735","stating the time, place  and  purposes  of  the  meeting,  shall be given by the"
"736","Trustees in accordance with the Declaration, mailed or sent  at  least  (ten) 10"
"737","days  and  not  more than ninety (90) days before the meeting. Only the business"
"738","stated in the notice  of  the  meeting  shall be considered at such meeting. Any"
"739","adjourned meeting may be held as adjourned  without  further notice, even if the"
"740","date  of such adjourned meeting is more than 90 days after  the  notice  of  the"
"741","meeting  was  mailed  or  sent.  Notwithstanding  the  foregoing,  if either the"
"742","President  or  Clerk  of the Trust, or in the absence or unavailability  of  the"
"743","President and the Clerk,  any  officer of the Trust, determines that as a result"
"744","of force majeure or an act of God or war, the date, time or place designated for"
"745","a meeting or adjourned meeting of  Shareholders is not reasonably practicable or"
"746","available, such officer may, without  further  notice to Shareholders, designate"
"747","such other date, time or place for such meeting  or  adjourned  meeting  as such"
"748","officer shall, in his or her sole discretion, determine. No notice need be given"
"749","to  any  Shareholder  who  shall  have failed to inform the Trust of his current"
"750","address or if a written waiver of notice,  executed  before or after the meeting"
"751","by  the  Shareholder or his attorney thereunto authorized,  is  filed  with  the"
"752","records of the meeting."
"753","      SECTION  3.  RECORD  DATE FOR MEETINGS. For the purpose of determining the"
"754","Shareholders who are entitled  to  notice  of  and to vote at any meeting, or to"
"755","participate in any distribution, or for the purpose  of  any  other  action, the"
"756","Trustees  may  from  time to time close the transfer books for such period,  not"
"757","exceeding thirty (30)  days,  as  the Trustees may determine; or without closing"
"758","the transfer books the Trustees may  fix  a  date not more than ninety (90) days"
"759","prior to the date of any meeting of Shareholders or distribution or other action"
"760","as  a  record  date  for  the determination of the  persons  to  be  treated  as"
"761","Shareholders of record for  such  purpose. The Trustees also may select the time"
"762","of  day  as  of which the calculations  for  determining  how  many  votes  each"
"763","Shareholder is entitled to pursuant to the Declaration shall be performed."
"764","      SECTION  4.  PROXIES. At any meeting of Shareholders, any holder of Shares"
"765","entitled to vote thereat  may  vote  by  proxy,  provided that no proxy shall be"
"766","voted at any meeting unless it shall have been placed on file with the Clerk, or"
"767","with  such  other officer or agent of the Trust as the  Clerk  may  direct,  for"
"768","verification  prior to the time at which such vote shall be taken. Pursuant to a"
"769","vote of a majority  of the Trustees, proxies may be solicited in the name of one"
"770","or more Trustees or one  or more of the officers of the Trust. When any Share is"
"771","held jointly by several persons,  any  one  of  them  may vote at any meeting in"
"772","person  or  by proxy in respect of such Share (and a proxy  shall  be  valid  if"
"773","executed by any  one  of them), but if more than one of them shall be present at"
"774","such meeting in person  or  by  proxy, and such joint owners or their proxies so"
"775","present disagree as to any vote to  be  cast, such vote shall not be received in"
"776","respect of such Share. A proxy purporting  to  be  executed by or on behalf of a"
"777","Shareholder shall be deemed valid unless challenged at or prior to its exercise,"
"778","and the burden of proving invalidity shall rest on the  challenger.  The placing"
"779","of  a  Shareholder's  name  on  a proxy pursuant to telephonic or electronically"
"780","transmitted instructions obtained  pursuant to procedures reasonably designed to"
"781","verify that such instructions have been  authorized  by  such  Shareholder shall"
"782","constitute execution of such proxy by or on behalf of such Shareholder.  If  the"
"783","holder  of any such Share is a minor or a person of unsound mind, and subject to"
"784","guardianship  or  to the legal control of any other person as regards the charge"
"785","or management of such  Share,  he  may vote by his guardian or such other person"
"786","appointed or having such control, and  such  vote  may  be given in person or by"
"787","proxy. Any copy, facsimile telecommunication or other reliable reproduction of a"
"788","proxy may be substituted for or used in lieu of the original  proxy  for any and"
"789","all  purposes  for  which  the original proxy could be used, provided that  such"
"790","copy, facsimile telecommunication  or  other  reproduction  shall  be a complete"
"791","reproduction of the entire original proxy or the portion thereof to  be returned"
"792","by the Shareholder."
"793","      SECTION  5.  QUORUM  AND  ADJOURNMENT.   Except  when  a larger quorum  is"
"794","required by any provision of law, Shares representing a majority  of  the voting"
"795","power  of  the outstanding Shares entitled to vote shall constitute a quorum  at"
"796","any meeting  of  Shareholders,  except  that  where  any  provision  of law, the"
"797","Declaration or these By-laws requires that holders of any series or class  shall"
"798","vote  as a series or class, then Shares representing a majority (unless a larger"
"799","quorum  is  required  as  specified  above) of the voting power of the aggregate"
"800","number of Shares of that series or class  entitled to vote shall be necessary to"
"801","constitute a quorum for the transaction of  business by that series or class. In"
"802","the absence of a quorum, Shareholders entitled  to  cast  votes  representing  a"
"803","majority  of the voting power of the outstanding Shares entitled to vote present"
"804","in person or  by proxy, or, where any provision of law, the Declaration or these"
"805","By-laws requires  that  holders of any series or class shall vote as a series or"
"806","class, Shareholders entitled to cast votes representing a majority of the voting"
"807","power of the outstanding Shares of that series or class entitled to vote present"
"808","in person or by proxy, may  adjourn the meeting from time to time until a quorum"
"809","shall be present. Only Shareholders  of  record shall be entitled to vote on any"
"810","matter."
"811","      SECTION 6. INSPECTION OF RECORDS. The  records  of the Trust shall be open"
"812","to inspection by Shareholders to the same extent as is permitted shareholders of"
"813","a Massachusetts business corporation."
"814","      SECTION  7.  ACTION  WITHOUT MEETING. Any action which  may  be  taken  by"
"815","Shareholders may be taken without  a  meeting  if  Shareholders  holding  Shares"
"816","representing  a  majority of the voting power of the Shares entitled to vote  on"
"817","the matter (or such  larger  proportion thereof as shall be required by law, the"
"818","Declaration or these By-Laws for  approval of such matter) consent to the action"
"819","in writing and the written consents  are  filed with the records of the meetings"
"820","of Shareholders. Such consent shall be treated  for all purposes as a vote taken"
"821","at a meeting of Shareholders."
"822","                                   ARTICLE IV"
"823","                                    TRUSTEES"
"824","      SECTION 1. MEETINGS OF THE TRUSTEES. The Trustees  may in their discretion"
"825","provide  for regular or stated meetings of the Trustees. Notice  of  regular  or"
"826","stated meetings  need  not be given. Meetings of the Trustees other than regular"
"827","or stated meetings shall be held whenever called by the Chair of the Trustees or"
"828","by any one of the Trustees  at  the time being in office. Notice of the time and"
"829","place of each meeting other than  regular  or  stated meetings shall be given by"
"830","the Secretary or an Assistant Secretary, or the  Clerk  or an Assistant Clerk or"
"831","by the officer, Chair of the Trustees or other Trustee calling  the  meeting and"
"832","shall be mailed to each Trustee at least two days before the meeting,  or  shall"
"833","be  telegraphed,  cabled, or wirelessed or sent by facsimile or other electronic"
"834","means to each Trustee  at his usual or last known business or residence address,"
"835","or personally delivered  to him at least one day before the meeting. Such notice"
"836","may, however, be waived by any Trustee. Notice of a meeting need not be given to"
"837","any Trustee if a written waiver  of  notice, executed by him before or after the"
"838","meeting, is filed with the records of the meeting, or to any Trustee who attends"
"839","the meeting without protesting prior thereto  or at its commencement the lack of"
"840","notice to him. A notice or waiver of notice need  not specify the purpose of any"
"841","meeting. Except as provided by law the Trustees may meet by means of a telephone"
"842","conference circuit or similar communications equipment  by  means  of  which all"
"843","persons  participating  in  the  meeting  can  hear  each other, which telephone"
"844","conference meeting shall be deemed to have been held at  a  place  designated by"
"845","the  Trustees  at  the meeting. Participation in a telephone conference  meeting"
"846","shall constitute presence in person at such meeting."
"847","      SECTION 2. QUORUM  AND  MANNER OF ACTING. A majority of the Trustees shall"
"848","be  present at any regular or special  meeting  of  the  Trustees  in  order  to"
"849","constitute  a quorum for the transaction of business at such meeting and (except"
"850","as otherwise  required  by  law,  the Declaration or these By-Laws) the act of a"
"851","majority of the Trustees present at  any  such  meeting,  at  which  a quorum is"
"852","present,  shall  be  the  act  of  the  Trustees. In the absence of a quorum,  a"
"853","majority of the Trustees present may adjourn the meeting from time to time until"
"854","a quorum shall be present. Notice of an adjourned meeting need not be given."
"855","                                    ARTICLE V"
"856","                          COMMITTEES AND ADVISORY BOARD"
"857","      SECTION 1. EXECUTIVE AND OTHER COMMITTEES.  The  Trustees  by  vote  of  a"
"858","majority  of  all  the  Trustees  may  elect  from their own number an Executive"
"859","Committee to consist of not less than three (3)  Trustees  to hold office at the"
"860","pleasure of the Trustees which shall have the power to conduct  the  current and"
"861","ordinary business of the Trust while the Trustees are not in session,  including"
"862","the  purchase  and  sale  of securities and the designation of securities to  be"
"863","delivered upon redemption of  Shares  of the Trust, and such other powers of the"
"864","Trustees as the Trustees may, from time  to  time,  delegate  to  the  Executive"
"865","Committee  except  those  powers  which by law, the Declaration or these By-Laws"
"866","they  are  prohibited  from  delegating.  The  Trustees  may  also  elect  other"
"867","Committees from time to time,  the  number composing such Committees, the powers"
"868","conferred upon the same (subject to the  same limitations as with respect to the"
"869","Executive  Committee)  and  the term of membership  on  such  Committees  to  be"
"870","determined by the Trustees. The  Trustees  may  designate  a  Chair  of any such"
"871","Committee.  In  the  absence  of such designation a Committee may elect its  own"
"872","Chair."
"873","      SECTION 2. MEETING, QUORUM AND MANNER OF ACTING. The Trustees may:"
"874","            (i)   provide for stated meetings of any Committee;"
"875","            (ii)  specify the manner  of calling and notice required for special"
"876","                  meetings of any Committee;"
"877","            (iii) specify the number of  members  of  a  Committee  required  to"
"878","                  constitute  a  quorum and the number of members of a Committee"
"879","                  required  to  exercise  specified  powers  delegated  to  such"
"880","                  Committee;"
"881","            (iv)  authorize the making of decisions to exercise specified powers"
"882","                  by written assent  of  the  requisite  number  of members of a"
"883","                  Committee without a meeting; and"
"884","            (v)   authorize  the members of a Committee to meet by  means  of  a"
"885","                  telephone  conference   circuit   or   similar  communications"
"886","                  equipment by means of which all persons  participating  in the"
"887","                  meeting can hear each other."
"888","      Each Committee shall keep and maintain regular minutes of its meetings and"
"889","records of decisions taken without a meeting."
"890","      SECTION  3. ADVISORY BOARD. The Trustees may appoint an Advisory Board  to"
"891","consist in the first  instance  of  not  less than three (3) members. Members of"
"892","such  Advisory  Board  shall  not  be Trustees  or  officers  and  need  not  be"
"893","Shareholders. A member of such Advisory  Board shall hold office for such period"
"894","as the Trustees may by resolution provide.  Any  member of such board may resign"
"895","therefrom by a written instrument signed by him which  shall  take  effect  upon"
"896","delivery  to  the Trust. The Advisory Board shall have no legal powers and shall"
"897","not perform the  functions  of Trustees in any manner, such Advisory Board being"
"898","intended merely to act in an  advisory  capacity. Such Advisory Board shall meet"
"899","at such times and upon such notice as the Trustees may by resolution provide."
"900","                                   ARTICLE VI"
"901","                       OFFICERS AND CHAIR OF THE TRUSTEES"
"902","      SECTION 1. GENERAL PROVISIONS. The  officers  of  the  Trust  shall  be  a"
"903","President,  a  Treasurer  and a Clerk, who shall be elected by the Trustees.  In"
"904","addition, there shall be an  Independent  Chief Compliance Officer, who shall be"
"905","elected or appointed by a majority of the Trustees,  including a majority of the"
"906","Trustees  who  are not Interested Persons of the Trust (Interested  Trustees),"
"907","and otherwise in  accordance  with  rule 38a-1 (or any successor rule) under the"
"908","1940 Act, as such rule may be amended  from  time  to  time (Rule 38a-1).  The"
"909","Trustees may elect or appoint such other officers or agents  of the Trust as the"
"910","business  of  the  Trust may require, including one or more Vice  Presidents,  a"
"911","Secretary  and  one  or  more  Assistant  Secretaries,  one  or  more  Assistant"
"912","Treasurers, and one or  more Assistant Clerks.  The Trustees may delegate to any"
"913","officer of the Trust or Committee  the power to appoint any subordinate officers"
"914","or agents.  In addition, there shall  be  an  office  of  Chair of the Trustees,"
"915","which shall serve on behalf of the Trustees, but shall not  be  an office of the"
"916","Trust. The office of Chair of the Trustees may be held by more than  one person."
"917","Any  Chair  of  the  Trustees  shall  be  elected by a majority of the Trustees,"
"918","including a majority of the Independent Trustees."
"919","      SECTION 2. TERM OF OFFICE AND QUALIFICATIONS. Except as otherwise provided"
"920","by  law,  the  Declaration or these By-Laws, the  Chair  of  the  Trustees,  the"
"921","President, the Treasurer, the Clerk and the Independent Chief Compliance Officer"
"922","shall hold office  until  his  resignation  has been accepted by the Trustees or"
"923","until his respective successor shall have been duly elected and qualified, or in"
"924","each  case until he sooner dies, resigns, is removed  or  becomes  disqualified."
"925","All other officers shall hold office at the pleasure of the Trustees. Any two or"
"926","more offices  may  be held by the same person.  Any officer of the Trust may be,"
"927","but none need be, a  Trustee or Shareholder.  Any Chair of the Trustees shall be"
"928","an Independent Trustee,  shall  not  be  an officer of the Trust and may be, but"
"929","need not be, a Shareholder."
"930","      SECTION  3. REMOVAL AND RESIGNATION.  The  Trustees,  at  any  regular  or"
"931","special meeting  of  the  Trustees,  may remove any officer of the Trust with or"
"932","without cause by a vote or consent of  a majority of the Trustees, provided that"
"933","any removal of the Independent Chief Compliance  Officer  shall also require the"
"934","vote or consent of a majority of the Independent Trustees and  otherwise  be  in"
"935","accordance  with  the  provisions  of  Rule 38a-1.  The Trustees may at any time"
"936","remove any Chair of the Trustees with or without cause by a vote or consent of a"
"937","majority of the Trustees, including a majority of the Independent Trustees.  Any"
"938","officer or agent appointed by any officer  or  Committee  may be removed with or"
"939","without cause by such appointing officer or Committee (subject to the provisions"
"940","of  Rule  38a-1 in the case of the Independent Chief Compliance  Officer).   Any"
"941","officer of  the Trust or Chair of the Trustees may resign at any time by written"
"942","instrument signed  by him and delivered to the Trust.  Such resignation shall be"
"943","effective upon receipt  unless  specified  to  be  effective at some other time."
"944","Except to the extent expressly provided in a written  agreement  with the Trust,"
"945","no officer of the Trust or Chair of the Trustees resigning or removed shall have"
"946","any  right  to  any  compensation  for  any period following his resignation  or"
"947","removal, or any right to damages on account of such removal."
"948","      SECTION 4. POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE  CHAIR OF THE TRUSTEES. The powers and"
"949","duties of the Chair of the Trustees shall include  (i)  calling  meetings of the"
"950","Trustees  when  deemed  necessary, (ii) setting the agenda for meetings  of  the"
"951","Trustees with input from officers of the Trust and, as necessary or appropriate,"
"952","the Trust's Investment Adviser  and  other service providers, (iii) presiding at"
"953","all meetings of the Trustees, (iv) presiding  at  all  meetings of Shareholders,"
"954","except  that  the  Chair  of the Trustees may appoint the President  or  another"
"955","officer of the Trust to preside  at  such  meetings in place of the Chair of the"
"956","Trustees, (v) acting as a liaison between the  Board of Trustees and the Trust's"
"957","officers,  Investment Adviser and other service providers  and  (vi)  exercising"
"958","such other powers and duties relating to the operations of the Trustees as, from"
"959","time to time,  may be conferred upon or assigned to such office by the Trustees,"
"960","provided that the  Chair  of  the Trustees shall have no individual authority to"
"961","act  for  the  Trust  as  an  officer   of  the  Trust.   In  carrying  out  the"
"962","responsibilities and duties of the office,  the  Chair  of the Trustees may seek"
"963","assistance and input from other Trustees or Committees of the Trustees, officers"
"964","of the Trust and the Trust's Investment Adviser and other  service providers, as"
"965","deemed necessary or appropriate. In the absence or disability  of  the  Chair of"
"966","the  Trustees,  a  majority  of  the  Trustees,  including  a  majority  of  the"
"967","Independent Trustees, shall appoint an Independent Trustee to perform the duties"
"968","and  exercise the powers of the Chair of the Trustees, provided that, unless and"
"969","until   such  appointment  is  made,  all  of  the  Independent  Trustees  shall"
"970","collectively perform such duties and exercise such powers."
"971","      SECTION  5. POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE PRESIDENT.  Subject to the control of"
"972","the Trustees, the  Chair of the Trustees and any Committees of the Trustees, the"
"973","President shall at all  times  exercise a general supervision and direction over"
"974","the affairs of the Trust, including  the  power  to employ attorneys and counsel"
"975","for  the  Trust  and  to employ such subordinate officers,  agents,  clerks  and"
"976","employees as he may find  necessary  to  transact the business of the Trust. The"
"977","President shall be the chief executive officer of the Trust. The President shall"
"978","have the power to grant, issue, execute or sign such powers of attorney, proxies"
"979","or other documents as may be deemed advisable or necessary in furtherance of the"
"980","interests of the Trust. The President shall  perform such other duties as may be"
"981","assigned to him from time to time by the Trustees or the Chair of the Trustees."
"982","      SECTION  6.  POWERS  AND  DUTIES OF VICE PRESIDENTS.  In  the  absence  or"
"983","disability of the President, the  Vice  President  or, if there be more than one"
"984","Vice President, any Vice President designated by the  Trustees shall perform all"
"985","the duties and may exercise any of the powers of the President,  subject  to the"
"986","control of the Trustees. Each Vice President shall perform such other duties  as"
"987","may be assigned to him from time to time by the Trustees or the President."
"988","      SECTION  7. POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE TREASURER. The Treasurer shall be the"
"989","principal financial  and  accounting  officer  of the Trust. The Treasurer shall"
"990","deliver all funds of the Trust which may come into  his  hands to such custodian"
"991","as the Trustees may employ. The Treasurer shall render a statement  of condition"
"992","of the finances of the Trust to the Trustees as often as they shall require  the"
"993","same  and  shall  in  general  perform  all the duties incident to the office of"
"994","Treasurer and such other duties as from time  to  time may be assigned to him by"
"995","the Trustees. The Treasurer shall give a bond for the  faithful discharge of his"
"996","duties, if required to do so by the Trustees, in such sum  and  with such surety"
"997","or sureties as the Trustees shall require."
"998","      SECTION  8.  POWERS  AND  DUTIES  OF THE CLERK. The Clerk shall  keep  the"
"999","minutes of all meetings of the Shareholders  in  proper  books provided for that"
"1000","purpose; he shall have custody of the seal of the Trust; he shall have charge of"
"1001","the Share transfer books, lists and records unless the same are in the charge of"
"1002","the Transfer Agent. He or the Secretary, if any, shall attend  to the giving and"
"1003","serving of all notices by the Trust in accordance with the provisions  of  these"
"1004","By-Laws  and  as  required  by  law;  and  subject to these By-Laws, he shall in"
"1005","general perform all duties incident to the office of Clerk and such other duties"
"1006","as from time to time may be assigned to him by the Trustees."
"1007","      SECTION  9. POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE SECRETARY.  The  Secretary,  if  any,"
"1008","shall keep the minutes  of  all  meetings of the Trustees. He shall perform such"
"1009","other duties and have such other powers  in addition to those specified in these"
"1010","By-Laws  as the Trustees shall from time to  time  designate.  If  there  be  no"
"1011","Secretary  or  Assistant  Secretary,  the  Clerk  shall  perform  the  duties of"
"1012","Secretary."
"1013","      SECTION  10. POWERS AND DUTIES OF ASSISTANT TREASURERS. In the absence  or"
"1014","disability of the  Treasurer, any Assistant Treasurer designated by the Trustees"
"1015","shall perform all the  duties,  and  may  exercise  any  of  the  powers, of the"
"1016","Treasurer. Each Assistant Treasurer shall perform such other duties as from time"
"1017","to  time may be assigned to him by the Trustees. Each Assistant Treasurer  shall"
"1018","give  a  bond  for the faithful discharge of his duties, if required to do so by"
"1019","the Trustees, in such sum and with such surety or sureties as the Trustees shall"
"1020","require."
"1021","      SECTION 11.  POWERS  AND  DUTIES  OF  ASSISTANT  CLERKS. In the absence or"
"1022","disability of the Clerk, any Assistant Clerk designated  by  the  Trustees shall"
"1023","perform  all the duties, and may exercise any of the powers, of the  Clerk.  The"
"1024","Assistant  Clerks  shall  perform  such other duties as from time to time may be"
"1025","assigned to them by the Trustees."
"1026","      SECTION 12. POWERS AND DUTIES  OF ASSISTANT SECRETARIES. In the absence or"
"1027","disability of the Secretary, any Assistant  Secretary designated by the Trustees"
"1028","shall perform all of the duties, and may exercise  any  of  the  powers,  of the"
"1029","Secretary.  The  Assistant  Secretaries  shall perform such other duties as from"
"1030","time to time may be assigned to them by the Trustees."
"1031","      SECTION 13. POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE INDEPENDENT CHIEF COMPLIANCE OFFICER."
"1032","The Independent Chief Compliance Officer shall  perform  the duties and have the"
"1033","responsibilities of the chief compliance officer of the Trust in accordance with"
"1034","Rule   38a-1,  and  shall  perform  such  other  duties  and  have  such   other"
"1035","responsibilities  as  from  time to time may be assigned to him by the Trustees."
"1036","The Independent Chief Compliance  Officer  shall report directly to the Trustees"
"1037","or a Committee of the Trustees in carrying out his functions."
"1038","      SECTION  14. COMPENSATION OF OFFICERS AND  TRUSTEES  AND  MEMBERS  OF  THE"
"1039","ADVISORY BOARD.  Subject  to any applicable law or provision of the Declaration,"
"1040","the compensation of the officers  of the Trust and Trustees (including the Chair"
"1041","of the Trustees) and members of the  Advisory  Board shall be fixed from time to"
"1042","time by the Trustees or, in the case of officers,  by  any  Committee or officer"
"1043","upon  whom  such  power  may  be  conferred by the Trustees, provided  that  any"
"1044","compensation of the Independent Chief  Compliance Officer shall be approved by a"
"1045","majority of the Trustees, including a majority  of the Independent Trustees.  No"
"1046","officer shall be prevented from receiving such compensation  as  such officer by"
"1047","reason of the fact that he is also a Trustee."
"1048","                                   ARTICLE VII"
"1049","                                   FISCAL YEAR"
"1050","      The fiscal year of the Trust shall be as specified on Appendix  A  hereto,"
"1051","provided,  however,  that  the  Trustees may from time to time change the fiscal"
"1052","year of the Trust or any series."
"1053","                                  ARTICLE VIII"
"1054","                                      SEAL"
"1055","      The Trustees may adopt a seal  which  shall be in such form and shall have"
"1056","such inscription thereon as the Trustees may from time to time prescribe."
"1057","                                   ARTICLE IX"
"1058","                                WAIVERS OF NOTICE"
"1059","      Whenever any notice is required to be given  by  law,  the  Declaration or"
"1060","these  By-Laws,  a  waiver  thereof in writing, signed by the person or  persons"
"1061","entitled to such notice, whether  before or after the time stated therein, shall"
"1062","be deemed equivalent thereto. A notice shall be deemed to have been telegraphed,"
"1063","cabled or wirelessed or sent by facsimile  or  other  electronic  means  for the"
"1064","purposes of these By-Laws when it has been delivered to a representative of  any"
"1065","telegraph,  cable  or  wireless company with instruction that it be telegraphed,"
"1066","cabled or wirelessed or  when a confirmation of such facsimile having been sent,"
"1067","or  a  confirmation  that such  electronic  means  has  sent  the  notice  being"
"1068","transmitted, is generated.  Any  notice  shall be deemed to be given at the time"
"1069","when the same shall be mailed, telegraphed, cabled or wirelessed or when sent by"
"1070","facsimile or other electronic means."
"1071","                                    ARTICLE X"
"1072","                           SALE OF SHARES OF THE TRUST"
"1073","      The Trustees may from time to time issue  and  sell  or cause to be issued"
"1074","and  sold  Shares  for cash or other property. The Shares, including  additional"
"1075","Shares which may have  been  repurchased by the Trust (herein sometimes referred"
"1076","to as treasury shares), may  not  be  sold  at a price less than the net asset"
"1077","value thereof (as defined in Article XI hereof)  determined  by  or on behalf of"
"1078","the Trustees next after the sale is made or at some later time after such sale."
"1079","      No Shares need be offered to existing Shareholders before being offered to"
"1080","others.  No  Shares  shall  be  sold  by  the  Trust (although Shares previously"
"1081","contracted to be sold may be issued upon payment  therefor)  during  any  period"
"1082","when  the determination of net asset value is suspended. In connection with  the"
"1083","acquisition  by merger or otherwise of all or substantially all the assets of an"
"1084","investment company  (whether  a  regulated  or  private  investment company or a"
"1085","personal holding company), the Trustees may issue or cause  to  be issued Shares"
"1086","and accept in payment therefor such assets valued at not more than  market value"
"1087","thereof  in lieu of cash, notwithstanding that the federal income tax  basis  to"
"1088","the Trust  of any assets so acquired may be less than the market value, provided"
"1089","that such assets  are  of  the  character in which the Trustees are permitted to"
"1090","invest the funds of the Trust."
"1091","                                   ARTICLE XI"
"1092","                            NET ASSET VALUE OF SHARES"
"1093","      The term net asset value  per  Share  of  any  class or series of Shares"
"1094","shall mean: (i) the value of all assets of that series or class; (ii) less total"
"1095","liabilities of such series or class; (iii) divided by the  number  of  Shares of"
"1096","such   series   or  class  outstanding,  in  each  case  at  the  time  of  such"
"1097","determination, all  as determine by or under the direction of the Trustees. Such"
"1098","value shall be determined  on  such  days  and  at such time as the Trustees may"
"1099","determine. Such determination shall be made with respect to securities for which"
"1100","market quotations are readily available, at the market value of such securities;"
"1101","and with respect to other securities and assets, at the fair value as determined"
"1102","in good faith by or pursuant to the direction of  the  Trustees  or  a Committee"
"1103","thereof, provided, however, that the Trustees, without shareholder approval, may"
"1104","alter  the method of appraising portfolio securities insofar as permitted  under"
"1105","the 1940  Act,  including  use  of  the  amortized cost method. The Trustees may"
"1106","delegate any powers and duties under this  Article  XI with respect to appraisal"
"1107","of  assets and liabilities. At any time the Trustees may  cause  the  value  per"
"1108","share last determined to be determined again in a similar manner and may fix the"
"1109","time when such predetermined value shall become effective. Determinations of net"
"1110","asset  value  made  by  the  Trustees  or their delegates in good faith shall be"
"1111","binding on all parties concerned."
"1112","                                   ARTICLE XII"
"1113","                           DIVIDENDS AND DISTRIBUTIONS"
"1114","      SECTION 1. LIMITATIONS ON DISTRIBUTIONS.  The  total  of  distributions to"
"1115","Shareholders of a particular series or class paid in respect of any  one  fiscal"
"1116","year, subject to the exceptions noted below, shall, when and as declared by  the"
"1117","Trustees, be approximately equal to the sum of:"
"1118","            (i)   the  net  income,  exclusive of the profits or losses realized"
"1119","                  upon the sale of securities  or other property, of such series"
"1120","                  or class for such fiscal year,  determined  in accordance with"
"1121","                  generally  accepted  accounting  principles  (which,   if  the"
"1122","                  Trustees  so  determine,  may  be  adjusted  for  net  amounts"
"1123","                  included as such accrued net income in the price of Shares  of"
"1124","                  such  series  or  class issued or repurchased), but if the net"
"1125","                  income of such series  or class exceeds the amount distributed"
"1126","                  by less than one cent per share outstanding at the record date"
"1127","                  for  the  final dividend,  the  excess  shall  be  treated  as"
"1128","                  distributable income of such series or class for the following"
"1129","                  fiscal year; and"
"1130","(ii)        in the discretion  of the Trustees, an additional amount which shall"
"1131","                  not substantially  exceed the excess of profits over losses on"
"1132","                  sales of securities  or  other property allocated or belonging"
"1133","                  to such series or class for such fiscal year; and"
"1134","(iii)       In discretion of the Trustees, an additional amount from other Trust"
"1135","                  assets."
"1136","The decision of the Trustees as to what, in  accordance  with generally accepted"
"1137","accounting  principles,  is  income and what is principal shall  be  final,  and"
"1138","except as specifically provided  herein  the decision of the Trustees as to what"
"1139","expenses and charges of the Trust shall be  charged  against  principal and what"
"1140","against income shall be final, all subject to any applicable provisions  of  the"
"1141","1940  Act.  For the purposes of the limitation imposed by this Section 1, Shares"
"1142","issued pursuant  to  Section 2 of this Article XII shall be valued at the amount"
"1143","of cash which the Shareholders  would  have  received  if  they  had  elected to"
"1144","receive cash in lieu of such Shares."
"1145","      Inasmuch as the computation of net income and gains for federal income tax"
"1146","purposes  may  vary from the computation thereof on the books of the Trust,  the"
"1147","above provisions shall be interpreted to give to the Trustees the power in their"
"1148","discretion to distribute  for  any  fiscal  year  as  ordinary  dividends and as"
"1149","capital  gains  distributions,  respectively,  additional amounts sufficient  to"
"1150","enable the Trust to avoid or reduce liability for  taxes.  Any  payment  made to"
"1151","Shareholders pursuant to clause (ii) and/or clause (iii) of this Section 1 shall"
"1152","be  accompanied  by  a  written  statement showing the source or sources of such"
"1153","payment, and the basis of computation thereof."
"1154","      SECTION 2. DISTRIBUTIONS PAYABLE  IN  CASH  OR  SHARES. The Trustees shall"
"1155","have power, to the fullest extent permitted by the laws  of  The Commonwealth of"
"1156","Massachusetts but subject to the limitation as to cash distributions  imposed by"
"1157","Section  1 of this Article XII, at any time or from time to time to declare  and"
"1158","cause to be paid distributions payable at the election of any Shareholder of any"
"1159","series or  class  (whether  exercised  before  or  after  the declaration of the"
"1160","distribution) either in cash or in Shares of such series, provided  that the sum"
"1161","of:"
"1162","            (i)   the cash distribution actually paid to any Shareholder, and"
"1163","            (ii)  the  net  asset  value  of  the  Shares which that Shareholder"
"1164","                  elects to receive, in effect at such  time  at  or  after  the"
"1165","                  election  as  the  Trustees  may specify, shall not exceed the"
"1166","                  full  amount  of  cash  to  which that  Shareholder  would  be"
"1167","                  entitled if he elected to receive only cash."
"1168","In the case of a distribution payable in cash or  Shares  at  the  election of a"
"1169","Shareholder,  the  Trustees  may  prescribe  whether  a Shareholder, failing  to"
"1170","express his election before a given time shall be deemed to have elected to take"
"1171","Shares rather than cash, or to take cash rather then Shares,  or  to take Shares"
"1172","with cash adjustment of fractions."
"1173","      The  Trustees,  in  their sole discretion, may cause the Trust to  require"
"1174","that all distributions payable to a shareholder in amounts less than such amount"
"1175","or amounts determined from  time  to  time  by  the  Trustees  be  reinvested in"
"1176","additional  shares  of  the Trust rather than paid in cash, unless a shareholder"
"1177","who, after notification that  his distributions will be reinvested in additional"
"1178","shares  in  accordance  with  the  preceding  phrase,  elects  to  receive  such"
"1179","distributions in cash. Where a shareholder  has elected to receive distributions"
"1180","in cash and the postal or other delivery service  is unable to deliver checks to"
"1181","the shareholder's address of record, the Trustees, in their sole discretion, may"
"1182","cause  the  Trust  to  require that such Shareholder's  distribution  option  be"
"1183","converted to having all distributions reinvested in additional shares."
"1184","      SECTION 3. STOCK DIVIDENDS.  Anything  in  these  By-Laws  to the contrary"
"1185","notwithstanding,  the Trustees may at any time declare and distribute  pro  rata"
"1186","among the Shareholders  of  any series or class a stock dividend out of either"
"1187","authorized but unissued Shares  of  such  series  or class or treasury Shares of"
"1188","such series or class or both."
"1189","                                  ARTICLE XIII"
"1190","                                   AMENDMENTS"
"1191","      These  By-Laws,  or  any  of them, may be altered,  amended,  repealed  or"
"1192","restated, or new By-Laws may be adopted,  at any time by the Trustees. Action by"
"1193","the Trustees with respect to the By-Laws shall  be  taken by an affirmative vote"
"1194","of a majority of the Trustees."
